  <DIV class="bluebox">
  <P><B>Three axis neutron spectrometer with flat-cone analyzer arrangement.</B></P>
  <P>
  The analyzer is put in flat-cone geometry by setting properties 
	in the <code> Instrument setup / Interface </code> dialog. Set option <i>flat-cone analyzer</i> = on/off.
  </P>
  <P>
  Set option <i>Q off-plane</i> = on to choose the mode with tilted flatcone: keeps AB plane in the horizontal position
  if Q is out of this plane. Otherwise, the sample is tilted to keep Q horizontal.
  </P>
  <P>
  Use the commands in the script <code>TAS_flatcone.inp</code> to try this example. 
  </P>  
  <P> 
  <I>Remarks:</I><BR />
  Use the commands in the attached *.inp script to perform various settings and commands.<BR />
  You can open the script in the Tools/Script editor and run selected blocks (select text by mouse, then "Run selected"). See the comments at the command blocks in the scripts for brief explanations.
  </P>   
  </DIV>
]]>
